<h2>Generating a Location Score</h2>

<p>To generate a Location Score, you'll need to supply the API with latitude and longitude coordinates of your query location. For example:</p>

<code>GET http://api.shutupseattle.com/score?latitude=47.63619109&longitude=-122.34287009</code>

<p>A successful result will look like this:</p>

<pre>
{
  "score":"F",
  "noises":[
    {
      "noise_type":"1 Demolition Site",
      "icon":"wrench",
      "details":[
        "Demolish existing single family residence subject to field inspection."
      ]
    },
    {
      "noise_type":"1 Bar",
      "icon":"glass",
      "details":null
    },
    {
      "noise_type":"2 Transit Stops",
      "icon":"road",
      "details":null
    },
    {
      "noise_type":"1 Freeway",
      "icon":"road",
      "details":null
    }
  ]
}
</pre>

<p><strong>Note:</strong> The API will return an error message if your query is outside of Seattle city limits. We roughly define that area as latitudes between <code>47.48172</code> and <code>47.734145</code>, and longitudes between <code>-122.224433</code> and <code>-122.459696</code>.</p>
